230
00:06:12.810 --> 00:06:14.940
right, kid?

231
00:06:14.940 --> 00:06:16.730
I appreciate it!

232
00:06:25.450 --> 00:06:28.030
<b>MONKEY</b>

233
00:06:35.670 --> 00:06:36.920
Boss?!

234
00:06:36.920 --> 00:06:38.210
What's the matter?!

235
00:06:38.210 --> 00:06:40.000
Are you sick?!

236
00:06:40.670 --> 00:06:44.930
I'm just glad those kids are safe...!

237
00:06:46.970 --> 00:06:50.770
I was... so worried...

238
00:07:09.080 --> 00:07:10.740
Look! That's...

239
00:07:12.750 --> 00:07:14.620
God's ship...

240
00:07:19.790 --> 00:07:21.380
It's God!

241
00:07:25.420 --> 00:07:26.590
They're sinking...

242
00:07:28.430 --> 00:07:31.310
God Enel and his ship are...

243
00:07:31.760 --> 00:07:33.770
sinking...

244
00:07:39.230 --> 00:07:41.070
The sound of that bell...

245
00:07:41.480 --> 00:07:46.360
is known as the Light of Shandora,
which rings in the glory of that ancient city.

246
00:07:50.870 --> 00:07:56.580
It's the song of the island
that declares this conflict over...

247
00:07:58.040 --> 00:08:03.300
After 400 long years,
the bell rang as promised...

248
00:08:15.350 --> 00:08:18.390
Although this restless floating island's
journey was long,

249
00:08:18.390 --> 00:08:20.940
its distant memories
are not easily forgotten.

250
00:08:21.810 --> 00:08:25.990
Its people once entrusted the sound
of that bell with a message...

251
00:08:31.740 --> 00:08:37.960
so that their proud words
would ring out across the vast sea.

252
00:08:42.130 --> 00:08:43.880
My friends...!

253
00:08:49.550 --> 00:08:51.300
It rang...

254
00:08:51.760 --> 00:08:52.680
Yeah.

255
00:08:54.100 --> 00:08:56.680
I wonder if chestnut head
and his friends heard it...

256
00:08:57.020 --> 00:08:59.480
They did. I'm sure of it.

257
00:09:08.820 --> 00:09:11.490
We are here!

258
00:09:17.160 --> 00:09:21.000
Tie the ropes to some
sturdy-looking trees!

259
00:09:52.860 --> 00:09:53.990
Aisa...

260
00:09:54.620 --> 00:09:56.120
Were you worried?

261
00:09:56.580 --> 00:09:59.540
Here... your treasure!

262
00:09:59.950 --> 00:10:02.410
I don't care about that!

263
00:10:04.250 --> 00:10:05.630
Raki...

264
00:10:15.470 --> 00:10:16.140
The others...

265
00:10:16.140 --> 00:10:17.180
They're fine!

266
00:10:17.180 --> 00:10:18.760
Just save your energy...

267
00:10:19.390 --> 00:10:20.640
Someone's there!

268
00:10:21.770 --> 00:10:24.730
I'm... still alive?

269
00:10:24.730 --> 00:10:27.570
No! We have to treat you right away!

270
00:10:27.940 --> 00:10:29.480
My treatment can wait.

271
00:10:29.480 --> 00:10:30.530
Huh?!

272
00:10:30.530 --> 00:10:34.950
I'll be fine. You should help him first.

273
00:10:34.950 --> 00:10:36.410
He's barely even alive.

274
00:10:46.290 --> 00:10:48.750
You're right!
His whole body is falling apart!

275
00:10:48.750 --> 00:10:50.130
This is terrible!

276
00:10:50.130 --> 00:10:53.010
Hey, that's one of the guerrillas.

277
00:10:53.010 --> 00:10:54.510
We don't owe him anything.

278
00:10:54.510 --> 00:10:55.760
True.

279
00:10:55.760 --> 00:10:57.970
I don't really know why...

280
00:10:58.300 --> 00:11:00.680
but it felt like he was
risking his life, so...

281
00:11:00.680 --> 00:11:01.680
Huh?

282
00:11:01.680 --> 00:11:04.520
What the heck?
You feeling sorry for him?

283
00:11:04.940 --> 00:11:05.980
Who knows...?

284
00:11:07.810 --> 00:11:08.900
Um...

285
00:11:09.520 --> 00:11:11.650
Is he gonna be okay, little tanuki?

286
00:11:11.650 --> 00:11:14.400
I'm a reindeer! Look, I have antlers!

287
00:11:15.360 --> 00:11:17.950
Don't worry. He'll survive.

288
00:11:18.950 --> 00:11:20.120
Thank you!

289
00:11:23.910 --> 00:11:28.250
Pierre, you should rest
with those Blue Sea folks.

290
00:11:33.550 --> 00:11:37.130
Pierre, hurry and bring the families!

291
00:11:40.640 --> 00:11:46.100
So in the end, the golden bell
and Enel's golden ship...

292
00:11:46.940 --> 00:11:48.810
...both fell, right?

293
00:11:50.230 --> 00:11:53.690
I guess now it's the City of Gold
in name only, huh?

294
00:11:54.190 --> 00:11:57.660
Which means our journey
in poverty continues.

295
00:11:58.410 --> 00:12:00.780
Gold, schmold! I'd rather have
some of those dials!

296
00:12:00.780 --> 00:12:03.450
You can't find stuff like that
back on the Blue Sea!

297
00:12:03.450 --> 00:12:07.080
I just really hope Nami's alright...

298
00:12:07.080 --> 00:12:09.380
And I wonder where Conis could be...

299
00:12:14.380 --> 00:12:17.470
Is it okay to leave Wyper
with the Blue Sea dwellers?

300
00:12:17.470 --> 00:12:18.720
It's fine.

301
00:12:18.720 --> 00:12:21.390
Aisa seems to have
made friends with them.

302
00:12:21.390 --> 00:12:23.310
At any rate, we have to hurry.

303
00:12:23.310 --> 00:12:25.540
There's no point
if our enemies wake up.

304
00:12:25.540 --> 00:12:26.890
Gather those who can move!

305
00:12:27.520 --> 00:12:29.650
We'll send the priests to the clouds.

306
00:12:29.650 --> 00:12:31.020
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

307
00:12:32.980 --> 00:12:34.860
Are you done with him?

308
00:12:34.860 --> 00:12:37.150
Yeah. All he needs now is rest.

309
00:12:37.150 --> 00:12:41.950
Guuuys!

310
00:12:39.610 --> 00:12:40.700
Luffy!

311
00:12:47.200 --> 00:12:49.160
Nami my sweet!

312
00:12:49.500 --> 00:12:50.960
Conis my love!

313
00:12:50.960 --> 00:12:52.790
Luffy!

314
00:12:57.630 --> 00:12:59.260
You guys!

315
00:12:59.260 --> 00:13:01.470
I'm glad you're okay!

316
00:13:03.180 --> 00:13:05.810
I was so worried,
but I couldn't do anything.

317
00:13:05.810 --> 00:13:09.180
You were really that worried
about me, Conis?!

318
00:13:08.060 --> 00:13:09.180
Not a chance.

319
00:13:09.560 --> 00:13:11.440
What's in there? Food?

320
00:13:11.440 --> 00:13:12.440
Where'd you get it?

321
00:13:12.440 --> 00:13:16.150
We found the priests' food storage
on our way back through the forest.

322
00:13:16.150 --> 00:13:17.440
There was lots left.

323
00:13:17.440 --> 00:13:20.150
But how'd you get back down
from all the way up there?

324
00:13:20.150 --> 00:13:22.110
We used my Gum-Gum Balloon.

325
00:13:22.990 --> 00:13:24.870
By the way, Conis,
where's your old man?

326
00:13:24.870 --> 00:13:25.580
Huh?

327
00:13:26.580 --> 00:13:29.080
Well... um...

328
00:13:29.080 --> 00:13:30.540
he protected me...

329
00:13:31.120 --> 00:13:31.920
and then Enel...

330
00:13:37.420 --> 00:13:38.670
Don't tell me...

331
00:13:42.550 --> 00:13:44.220
Conis...

332
00:13:44.220 --> 00:13:46.100
Conis...

333
00:13:46.600 --> 00:13:48.060
Conis...

334
00:13:50.020 --> 00:13:52.140
– Wait, we're talking about you!
– Wait, we're talking about you!

335
00:13:52.140 --> 00:13:54.060
I'm sorry but I'm still alive!

336
00:13:54.980 --> 00:13:56.400
Father!

337
00:13:58.940 --> 00:14:00.440
The lower White Sea?

338
00:14:00.440 --> 00:14:04.280
Yes. I found myself there
after being knocked off.

339
00:14:04.280 --> 00:14:08.700
One by one, the people who fled to
the lower level toward Cloud End

340
00:14:08.700 --> 00:14:13.500
are returning to the White-White Sea
using the milky roads they restored.

341
00:14:13.500 --> 00:14:17.630
However, without
Angel Island to return to,

342
00:14:17.630 --> 00:14:21.340
they're all coming
to Upper Yard instead.

343
00:14:35.400 --> 00:14:37.900
– Thank you so much!
– Thank you so much, God!

344
00:14:38.650 --> 00:14:41.360
That is no longer who I am.

345
00:14:41.860 --> 00:14:45.530
To think that you were forced to work
in such a place for six long years...

346
00:14:45.530 --> 00:14:47.450
Please forgive me.

347
00:14:48.950 --> 00:14:52.700
We have no place to return home to.

348
00:14:52.700 --> 00:14:56.250
The Shandians have lost
the Village Hidden in the Clouds too.

349
00:14:56.580 --> 00:14:59.960
Is the fighting really over?

350
00:15:06.550 --> 00:15:08.970
God's Army is gone, but...

351
00:15:08.970 --> 00:15:14.020
Can we really mend
a 400-year-old rift that easily, Chief?

352
00:15:17.980 --> 00:15:19.310
Man, I'm stuffed!

353
00:15:19.310 --> 00:15:20.690
It's dark out now.

354
00:15:20.690 --> 00:15:22.150
Wanna head back to the ship?

355
00:15:22.150 --> 00:15:24.530
Nami, what're you saying?!

356
00:15:24.530 --> 00:15:25.860
What do you mean?!

357
00:15:25.860 --> 00:15:28.070
Usopp, are you hearing this?

358
00:15:28.070 --> 00:15:30.200
Yeah, how horrible.

359
00:15:30.200 --> 00:15:32.200
To say that after all this,

360
00:15:32.200 --> 00:15:34.790
you're a failure as a pirate–
No, as a human!

361
00:15:34.790 --> 00:15:38.210
What the heck
are you talking about?!

362
00:15:44.630 --> 00:15:49.300
I'm headed home
to where God belongs...

363
00:15:49.720 --> 00:15:55.430
Nothing in this sky must be
allowed to obscure my vision...

364
00:15:56.230 --> 00:15:59.310
All of you were in my way.

365
00:16:01.940 --> 00:16:06.070
No one else may have it.
It is fit only for me!

366
00:16:06.820 --> 00:16:10.200
This land without end,
like something from a dream!

367
00:16:11.280 --> 00:16:15.830
Now, let us go, Maxim...

368
00:16:15.830 --> 00:16:20.290
To the realm of the gods
that floats brightly in the night sky...

369
00:16:20.290 --> 00:16:22.460
To that boundless land...

370
00:16:22.460 --> 00:16:24.960
the Endless Vearth!

371
00:16:35.310 --> 00:16:36.730
Where am I?

372
00:16:36.730 --> 00:16:39.600
Inside the ruins of Shandora.

373
00:16:40.600 --> 00:16:42.230
Gan Fall!

374
00:16:42.230 --> 00:16:44.360
Oh, you shouldn't move yet.

375
00:16:44.360 --> 00:16:46.610
You... You're a Skypiean!

376
00:16:47.950 --> 00:16:49.860
Just rest for now.

377
00:16:50.570 --> 00:16:51.700
Chief!

378
00:16:51.700 --> 00:16:55.830
All of those injured in battle
will be treated the same.

379
00:16:55.830 --> 00:16:57.620
The golden bell...

380
00:16:57.620 --> 00:17:00.870
We still have a duty to protect it!

381
00:17:02.960 --> 00:17:04.460
This is...

382
00:17:05.170 --> 00:17:07.420
the sound of war drums!

383
00:17:08.130 --> 00:17:09.880
The ruins are on fire too?!

384
00:17:10.590 --> 00:17:12.260
Calm yourself, Wyper.

385
00:17:12.260 --> 00:17:14.760
Just be patient and observe.

386
00:17:14.760 --> 00:17:19.430
Whatever noble reasons there may
have once been to justify this conflict,

387
00:17:19.430 --> 00:17:21.850
to those of us who remain,

388
00:17:21.850 --> 00:17:23.940
this sky has already
long been our home.

389
00:17:23.940 --> 00:17:27.610
The land, at least,
is not refusing anyone.

390
00:17:27.610 --> 00:17:28.740
Indeed.

391
00:17:28.740 --> 00:17:31.820
Feel free to see it for yourself.

392
00:17:31.820 --> 00:17:35.030
For at the present moment...

393
00:17:35.030 --> 00:17:37.950
not one, single soul wants to fight.

394
00:17:51.130 --> 00:17:53.430
It's party time!

395
00:19:01.970 --> 00:19:07.490
When you're lost and alone, call out and lead me to your side

396
00:19:07.710 --> 00:19:12.910
As you wander far from home, you search the sky and never hide

397
00:19:12.910 --> 00:19:15.710
You are so much like the moon

398
00:19:15.710 --> 00:19:20.360
Calmer than a star, your twinkling's lost

399
00:19:23.810 --> 00:19:32.760
A deep reflection shines, you slowly leave, fading, and what's the cost?

400
00:19:32.820 --> 00:19:37.990
Stay as you are, don't lose your way

401
00:19:37.990 --> 00:19:46.300
Let my words guide you, and look ahead until the day!

402
00:19:46.940 --> 00:19:53.190
Don't give up on your dreams, through endless nights they come to you

403
00:19:53.190 --> 00:19:58.810
If you stop, you'll never see them shining through!

404
00:20:00.050 --> 00:20:04.580
Will you return? Maybe not... Will you learn? I hope you do

405
00:20:04.580 --> 00:20:10.970
Please put your past to rest, and live your life anew.
